x4freetext: The lohengrin spectrometer was used. It is
dispersive in two dimensions. The energy of the
fragments and the mass-to-charge ratio were
determined from measuring the horizontal
and vertical coordinates in a two-dimensional
ionization chamber. A delta-e signal was also
obtained from it.
.25 microgram of Cf2O3, enriched to 99.73%
in Cf-249, with an area of 2.5 X 20 mm2,
electrodeposited onto a titanium backing. The
target was covered with a 0.25 micrometer nickel
foil.
.Absolute fission yields were obtained by
normalizing to the absolute mass yield of a = 88
from djebara et Al (j,Np/a,496,346,89). The
results of djebara et Al have been renormalized
by a factor 1.022.
.Corrections for changes in the target properties
as a function of exposure time were applied.
.Gaussian-peak unfolding of the spectra.
.No direct information from main reference. It seems
likely that errors include both statistical and
fitting errors.
J.B.
